display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(238, 238, 238); line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.div:
1. distributor, factory, warehouse can all can check and manage their inventories (Central authority can see all) and also their stock capacity
2. C.A can approve or reject request of products by receiver, 3. C.A can suggest one how to manage its products (increase or decrease production or purchase of certain products)
4. All can see the suggestion by C.A for their inventory
5. Chat system with their direct ancestor in supply chain and transport
6. purchase order for warehouse and distributor
7. C.A and everyone can see the notification of events connected to them
8. factory, warehouse can prepare shipment manually or by scanning bar-code of products
9. After approval sender can send their shipment info transport
10. transport receives the shipment, select best vehicle with suggestion from sender and C.A
11. transport may design optimal path and publish it(may see suggestion for routes by sender or C.A)
12. transport may devise a plan for taking multiple shipment to multiple destination
13. transport may have tracking system of vehicle in route (can be send by sender, receiver and C.A)[extra: other can request to C.A for viewing certain or ongoing shipment]
14. may design a semi-automated system for producing or purchasing products by recent sales or other criteria
15. system for conflict resolution(of orders) and sending decisions(will send or wait even if products available) manually or may have semi automated system
